Magmatic carbon emissions are easier to model than thermogenic
emissions because it is not necessary to track reaction kinetics.
Carbon is strongly incompatible in all primary minerals formed
during solidiﬁcation of basaltic sills. Almost all mantle-derived
carbon dioxide dissolved in the magma therefore exsolves shortly
before solidiﬁcation, mixes with the super-critical host-rock pore
ﬂuid, and escapes through hydrothermal vents along with ther-
mogenic methane. Our parameterisation is based on the same set
of sill and host-rock characteristics used for the thermogenic
